- Shows the list of simulators/devices
    xcrun simctl list devices

- Can either delete the individual device(s):
    xcrun simctl delete D24C18BC-268C-4F0B-9CD8-8EFFDE6619E3

- Or bulk delete all of the unavailable ones with:
    xcrun simctl delete unavailable



~/Library/Developer/CoreSimulator/Devices

Check how many simulators that you have downloaded as they take up a lot of space
~/Library/Developer/Xcode/iOS DeviceSupport

Also delete old archived apps:
~/Library/Developer/Xcode/Archives

You can also remove to free a lot of memory
~/Library/Developer/CoreSimulator/Caches/dyld/





===== How to uninstall simulator ======
Delete the particular simulator runtime references (*.simruntime) in the folder: 
/Library/Developer/CoreSimulator/Profiles/Runtimes

Delete the particular simulator images (*.dmg) in the folder: 
~/Library/Caches/com.apple.dt.Xcode/Downloads
